closed	backend	approve_proposal is not crash/failure-atomic: commit_index (git push, durable) and discord.proposal_approved (external) both run BEFORE the DB delete is committed, and delete_proposal is sequenced AFTER load_base (which can raise). The proposal row + delete live in the proposal_update FOR-UPDATE txn that only commits at the connection-block exit, so ANY failure after a successful push (discord error, load_base error, commit failure) rolls back the delete -> proposal stays in the DB while its change is already in the YAML + announced approved on Discord = orphaned 'approved but still open' proposal. Fix direction: once commit_index succeeds (point of no return) delete + commit the row before the non-critical steps, and make discord+load_base best-effort (try/except log, don't raise). NOTE: not the cause of the 3 current orphans (those are Sept-2024 legacy rows from the Quart version — their rulings are committed, only the DB cleanup never happened); this is forward-looking hardening.
