closed	backend	Normalize card tokens in ruling text to the card's unique_name. Today the {Card} token is stored verbatim as typed and only resolved at read time by krcg's FuzzyDict (difflib, cutoff 0.85) — so the repo holds non-canonical tokens: {Theo Bell (ADV)} (true unique_name 'Theo Bell (G2 ADV)'), {Jimmy Dunn (G2)} and {Louhi (G4)} (both cards are unique, no suffix at all). {Theo Bell (ADV)} scores close against BOTH 'theo bell (g2)' and 'theo bell (g2 adv)'; a krcg card-data change could silently flip which variant a ruling points at, and a near-miss token that stops matching becomes a KeyError at load. Fix: on ruling save (utils.build_ruling / parse_cards is where the card is already resolved) rewrite each token to '{' + card.unique_name + '}' so what is persisted is exactly what the FuzzyDict keys on. OPEN Q, decide before starting: ruling uid = stable_hash(text), so normalizing rewrites the uid of every affected ruling — that breaks existing #r-<uid> permalinks and any Discord thread linking them. Either accept the churn on the ~3 affected rulings and do a one-off pass over the repo, or normalize only on edit and leave existing text alone (drift stays until each is touched). parent:#66
